    <div class="intro">
      Use this checklist during code review or codebase audits to spot drift before it spreads.
      Check each item you find in your codebase, then score yourself at the bottom.
    </div>

    <div class="grid">
      <!-- Colors -->
      <div class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <span class="section-icon">üé®</span>
          <span class="section-title">Colors</span>
        </div>
        <ul class="checklist">
          <li><div class="checkbox"></div> Hardcoded hex values (<code>#3B82F6</code>) instead of tokens</li>
          <li><div class="checkbox"></div> RGB/HSL values that don't match any defined color</li>
          <li><div class="checkbox"></div> Slight variations of brand colors (<code>#3A81F5</code> vs <code>#3B82F6</code>)</li>
          <li><div class="checkbox"></div> Opacity hacks instead of defined color scales</li>
          <li><div class="checkbox"></div> Colors defined in component files, not imported from tokens</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Spacing -->
      <div class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <span class="section-icon">üìè</span>
          <span class="section-title">Spacing</span>
        </div>
        <ul class="checklist">
          <li><div class="checkbox"></div> Arbitrary pixel values (<code>padding: 13px</code>) outside your scale</li>
          <li><div class="checkbox"></div> Inconsistent spacing on similar components</li>
          <li><div class="checkbox"></div> Magic numbers with no explanation (<code>margin-top: 37px</code>)</li>
          <li><div class="checkbox"></div> Mixing units (px, rem, em) without a system</li>
          <li><div class="checkbox"></div> Tailwind arbitrary values (<code>p-[13px]</code>) instead of scale classes</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Typography -->
      <div class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <span class="section-icon">üî§</span>
          <span class="section-title">Typography</span>
        </div>
        <ul class="checklist">
          <li><div class="checkbox"></div> Font sizes that don't match your type scale</li>
          <li><div class="checkbox"></div> Hardcoded <code>font-family</code> declarations</li>
          <li><div class="checkbox"></div> Line heights that drift from defined ratios</li>
          <li><div class="checkbox"></div> Font weights outside your allowed set</li>
          <li><div class="checkbox"></div> Letter-spacing tweaks on individual components</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Components -->
      <div class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <span class="section-icon">üß©</span>
          <span class="section-title">Components</span>
        </div>
        <ul class="checklist">
          <li><div class="checkbox"></div> Inline styles overriding component defaults</li>
          <li><div class="checkbox"></div> <code>!important</code> used to force style changes</li>
          <li><div class="checkbox"></div> Wrapper divs adding custom spacing around components</li>
          <li><div class="checkbox"></div> Copy-pasted component code instead of imports</li>
          <li><div class="checkbox"></div> "One-off" components that duplicate existing patterns</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Scoring -->
    <div class="scoring">
      <h2>Score Yourself</h2>
      <div class="score-grid">
        <div class="score-item">
          <div class="score-range">0-3</div>
          <div class="score-label">Healthy</div>
        </div>
